## Service Name
principal_service_name.title                                    = Use software to send Income Tax updates
agent_service_name.title                                        = Use software to report your client''s Income Tax

## Overview Page Content
overview.title                                                  = The way you record Self Assessment is changing
overview.heading                                                = The way you record Self Assessment is changing
overview.line_1                                                 = Making Tax Digital for Income Tax is a new way for self-employed businesses (sole traders) and landlords to send income tax updates to HMRC.
overview.line_2                                                 = You can use software to keep your business records digitally and send income tax updates to HMRC, instead of filing a Self Assessment tax return.
overview.link_text                                              = Find out more about Making Tax Digital for income tax (opens in a new tab)

## Terms and Conditions Page ##
terms.title                                                     = Terms of participation
terms.heading                                                   = Terms of participation
terms.line1                                                     = By taking part in this pilot, you agree that you will:
terms.bullet1                                                   = use relevant software to record income and expenses
terms.bullet2                                                   = provide an email address so your client can be contacted by HMRC
terms.bullet3                                                   = submit a quarterly report from the start of your accounting period
terms.bullet4                                                   = send your final report by the 31 January at the end of their tax year
terms.bullet5                                                   = declare any other income sources and reliefs you have
terms.bullet6                                                   = tell HMRC if you stop trading or start a new business
terms.bullet7                                                   = submit reports using your usual method if you leave this pilot
terms.line2                                                     = You can stop taking part in this pilot at any time.

## Get Software
get_software.title                                              = You will need to get compatible software after signing up
get_software.heading                                            = You will need to get compatible software after signing up
get_software.line_1                                             = The software you use must be able to send income and expense reports to HMRC.
get_software.find_software                                      = Find software that''s compatible with Making Tax Digital for Income Tax (opens in a new tab)

## "Have you got software" page messages ##
have_you_got_software.title                                     = Do you currently use accounting software?
have_you_got_software.hint                                      = This does not include any spreadsheet software.
have_you_got_software.error                                     = Select yes if you currently use accounting software

## Check for Compatible Software
check_compatible_software.title                                 = Check that the software you use is compatible with Making Tax Digital for Income Tax
check_compatible_software.heading                               = Check that the software you use is compatible with Making Tax Digital for Income Tax
check_compatible_software.line                                  = You must check that your software can connect and send income and expense reports to HMRC.
check_compatible_software.link                                  = Check if your software is compatible (opens in a new tab)

## Do you have any other income page
have_any_other_income.title                                     = Do you have any sources of income other than self employment or property income?
have_any_other_income.include                                   = This could include:
have_any_other_income.notInclude                                = This does not include:
have_any_other_income.includePoint1                             = as an employee for another business
have_any_other_income.includePoint2                             = UK pensions or annuities
have_any_other_income.includePoint3                             = investments from outside the UK
have_any_other_income.includePoint4                             = capital gains
have_any_other_income.includePoint5                             = taxable state benefits
have_any_other_income.notIncludePoint1                          = bank and building society interest
have_any_other_income.notIncludePoint2                          = dividends
have_any_other_income.error.summary                             = Select yes if you have any sources of income other than self employment or property income

## Do you have any other income page errors
have_any_other_income_error.title                               = You cannot use this service yet
have_any_other_income_error.line1                               = This is a trial service. You may be able to use the ''Use software to send Income Tax updates'' service in the future.

## Terms and Conditions Page ##
agent.terms.title                                               = Terms of participation
agent.terms.heading                                             = Terms of participation
agent.terms.line1                                               = By taking part in this pilot, you agree that either you or your client will:
agent.terms.bullet1                                             = use relevant software to record income and expenses
agent.terms.bullet2                                             = provide an email address so your client can be contacted by HMRC
agent.terms.bullet3                                             = submit a quarterly report from the start of your client''s accounting period
agent.terms.bullet4                                             = send your client''s final report by the 31 January at the end of their tax year
agent.terms.bullet5                                             = tell HMRC if your client stops trading or starts a new business
agent.terms.bullet6                                             = submit reports using your usual method if your client leaves this pilot
agent.terms.line2                                               = These terms are not contractual and your client can stop taking part in this pilot at any time.
